00 for a computer but be a cheap ass and try to save 20 bucks on a fan and use some ghetto stock crap.<br>
<br>
Geforce is really easy to OC even a moron could do it. Not to familiar to ATI cause they haven't given me a reason to be. If you are a big computer nut (which it doesn't seem terribly like you are :P) then you would go for some serious cooling to overclock your PC to squeeze every lil bit o juice you can out of that mofo. Pick up the issue of September Maximum PC they built a dream machine and it's somewhere along the lines of what you are looking at.<br>
<br>
Who said computers have to be fugly? <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.harddrive.com">www.harddrive.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> They are the fashion in the computer world. Get yourself a case with a window, a neon light kit, some custom fan grills, and some black rope (to cover up the uglyness of the cables that connect to your PSU and increase circulation, yay circulation) and some clear rounded IDE cables(really just looks cool but you can tell people it helps increase circulation.)<br>
<br>
DVD RW is nice but are you really that in need? Remember when CD-RW was like 300 now its about 50. Well err basically. Point is, are you really going to use it enough that you are willing to have one that will be outdated and way overpriced? Not to mention some of the copyright crap that it just wont let you copy some stuff. Need some ninja to write some program to fix that but until then you are limited to a degree. Sure it's nice but that money could go somewhere better.<br>
<br>
Creative labs... best sound for best value. But do you really need the platinum series? Again something with neat features but mostly unnecessary. Doubt you will get much use of the little front feature.<br>
<br>
Thats a huge monitor... while you are on a wily spending spree: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.matrox.com/mga/">www.matrox.com/mga/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
