Cordless reset happens when you have both a keyboard and a mouse sharing a single receiver.  There is a button on the mouse and keyboard that has to be synced with the receiver when you first put in the batteries.  <br>
<br>
I have such weird luck with them but I abuse my keyboard.  I move it around, my daughter drops it, I hit the mouse on the desk in frustration when I lose a game of warcraft 3 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  The batteries jiggle and it causes the device to lose programming.  Hence the reset.<br>
<br>
[RDRam]<br>
I don't know if you can get a 2.5Gig using SDRam, wouldn't that require PC-166 Ram, and I don't know if he can get it easily at this time.  I don't like that RDRam is going away but if that's all you can use, that's all you can use.<br>
<br>
[120Gb WD Hard Drive]<br>
8Mb is the largest they make.  Also the largest Seagate Makes.  The only way he's gonna get a bigger cache is to go Maxtor.  And I HATE Maxtor<br>
<br>
[Single DVD Writer]<br>
Probably the only thing you are gonna regret is not getting a DVD/CD Reader with it.  Right about the time you start duping things.<br>
