<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Though RAID Level 0 is the fastest option of all, it is also the most precarious by far. For example, using four hard drives will push the data transfer rate far beyond 100 MB/s, but <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fault tolerance will be virtually non-existent.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A hard drive is a mechanical component that will age and wear out after a while. Mechanically-induced defects are therefore really only a question of time. But even an electronic error or a minor production error may result in a catastrophe<br>
